examples.en: It's a free country, ain't it?
Those people ain't got a clue.
In my opinion, my work ain't quite good enough.
Her husband left and she ain't never been the same.
I believe in the maxim 'if it ain't broke, don't fix it'.
Mr. F. shall introduce him.  It ain't a him, it's a her.
Your partner is a whole team, ain't he? He's a rattler! (M. Thompson)
In the immortal words of Henry Ford, 'If it ain't broke, don't fix it.'
Many English teachers cringe when their students use the word ain't.
My prints ain't on that gun. *
I ain't hipped on her any more. *
I ain't taught you how to sting. *
I ain't dead yet by a darn sight. *
I ain't done nothing, so help me. *
